Kingsley Burrell, 29, was arrested and sectioned in Birmingham city centre in March 2011 . 
  He was taken into custody after calling police to say he was threatened with a machine gun . 
  Mr Burrell died four days later at the Queen Elizabeth Hospital in Birmingham . 
  His sister told inquest he was handcuffed for six hours and wet himself . 
  She said he was denied access to a toilet and repeatedly punched by officers . 
  He had called police saying three men had threatened him with a gun . 
  But CCTV showed nobody had approached him and he was sectioned under Mental Health Act . 
  Inquest heard he was arrested after claiming he was being threatened with gun . 
 